Package org.jboss.windup.reporting.model

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ApplicationReportIndexModel
    This lists all of the top level reports within the application report (eg, Application classes report, Hibernate entity report, EJB report, etc).
    ApplicationReportModel
    These reports are directly associated with an application, and that application's project model.
    ClassificationModel
    This classifies files and provides general background information about a specific FileModel.
    FreeMarkerSourceReportModel
    This extends SourceReportModel with some functions that are used by our source rendering template.
    IgnoredFilesReportModel
    Report model containing all the information needed for the report listing all the ignored files during the windup process with all the ignore regexes they were matched against.
    InlineHintModel
    This is used to classify lines within application source FileModel instances, and to provide hints and related data regarding specific positions within those files.
    LinkModel
    Model saves an additional links for the InlineHintModel or ClassificationModel.
    OverviewReportLineMessageModel
    This classifies files and provides general background information about a specific FileModel.
    ReportFileModel
    Extends the file model with some convenience accessors for getting to InlineHintModel and other reporting related data.
    ReportModel
    Provides the base object for all reports.
    TechnologyTagModel
    Represents a technology that is used or implemented by a particular file.
    WindupVertexListModel<T extends WindupVertexFrame>
    Contains a list of WindupVertexFrame objects and (for convenience) implements the Iterable interface as well.
